                <section class="comment-body font-light"><p>Just got Ref 4 and love it! I understand why Safe Headroom feature is needed, but I am trying to understand the best way to work with this on and still have my mix at the levels I need them  &amp; how I have mixed up till this point. I always worked/mixed having a target around -9db RMS on Logic basic level meter, but now with a 10db cut using "safe headroom" I can't trust that meter. Is it as simple as inserting another meter right "before" Ref 4 does it's safety cut? Also, Is the safety cut amount exactly the db that would go over 0? Thanks!</p>
